label: abortivum
definition: In taxonomy, a name which contravened the Code in operation at the time.

label: alternativum
definition: An alternative name given in the original publication before 1953 based on the same type.

label: ambigua
definition: ambiguous name, one which has been used so long by different authors in different senses that it has become a persistent cause of error and  confusion.

label: available
definition: A name that is correctly proposed according to the International Code of  Zoological Nomenclature. An available name is not necessarily the valid  name.

label: combinatio
definition: The name is a new combination, i.e. a name change involving the epithet of  the basionym. ICBN: Name of the original author being kept within  parantheses.

label: confusum
definition: A name rejected if it is based on a type consisting of two or more entirely  discordant elements, so that it is difficult to select a satisfactory  lectotype.

label: conservandum
definition: a scientific name that enjoys special nomenclatural protection, i.e. a name  conserved in respective code. names classed as available and valid by action  of the ICZN or ICBN exercising its Plenary Powers . Includes rulings to  conserve junior/later synonyms in place of rejected forgotten names (nomen  oblitum). Such names are entered on the Official Lists.

label: correctum
definition: Corrected names or 'improved' names, available names which are mandatory and allowable emendations of imperfect names (qv) or of taxonomic names  higher than family (which are not subject to name form and ending  regulations). Do not depend on transfer in taxon rank or assignment. (= an  emended name).

label: dubimum
definition: A name of uncertain sense, of doubtful validity. E.g. the name Encephalartos tridentatus (Willdenow) Lehmann (Pugillus 6, 1834) is a nomen dubium which  may refer to several species of Encephalartos or Macrozamia. ICZN: doubtful  or dubious names, names which are not certainly applicable to any known  taxon or for which the evidence is insufficient to permit recognition of the  taxon to which they belong. May possess availability conducive to  uncertainty and instability. Also nullnames under enquirynull: NOMEN  INQUIRENDUM (NOMINA INQUIRENDA).

label: illegitimum
definition: nomen illegitimum: illegitimate name

label: invalidum
definition: invalid name

label: negatum
definition: denied names, unavailable names which are incorrect original spellings as  defined by the Code. Subset of nom.inval. based only on spellings

label: novum
definition: A scientific name that is created specifically to replace a name which is a  junior synonym or homonym. New name designated when a name cannot be used  for nomenclaturalpurposes and no type or original material exists. A name established expressly to replace an already established name. A nominal  taxon denoted by a new replacement name (nomen novum) has the same  name-bearing type as the nominal taxon denoted by the replaced name. ICZN:  new name which is expressly proposed as a replacement name for a preoccupied  name , automatically takes the same type and type locality. (= a replacement  name or substitute name for a preoccupied name). Commonly applied to names  proposed to replace junior homonyms. A name proposed as a substitute for a  previously published name (ICBN Art. 7.3 and 33.4).

label: nudum
definition: name without a description, i.e. a name not (or not yet) published with an  adequate description.

label: nullum
definition: null names, unavailable names which as defined by the Code are non demonstrably intentional changes of an original spelling i.e. a form of  incorrect subsequent spelling

label: oblitum
definition: a name that has not been used in the scientific community for more than  fifty years after its original proposal. forgotten names, senior synonyms which have remained unused in the literature for many years. Have been  treated differently by different editions of the Code, and remain  unavailable names.

label: oppressa
definition: suppressed publication in respective code

label: orthographia
definition: A spelling variation of a full combination (name and authorship) that may or  may not be a misspelling.

label: protectum
definition: protected name applied to a name which has been given precedence over it  unused senior synonym or senior homonym relegated to the status of nomen oblitum (see Article 23.9.2).

label: provisorium
definition: Provisional name, a name proposed in anticipation of the future acceptance of the taxon concerned, or of a particular circumscription, position, or  rank of the taxon (ICBN Art. 34.1).

label: rejiciendum
definition: Rejected in favour of. Inverse of conserved against

label: rejiciendumProp
definition: proposed rejected name. Temporary status until the next botanical congress decides about the proposal.

label: rejiciendumUtique
definition: Name rejected outright, i. e. without proposing another name to be conserved in favor of this name (nomen utique rejiciendum). This status applies to explicitly listed protonym names as well as to any combinations based on the protonym. See ICBN (Art. 56.1, Appendix V) because otherwise it would cause a disadvantageous nomenclatural change.

label: rejiciendumUtiqueProp
definition: proposed rejected name on the basis of appendix V of ICBN

label: superfluum
definition: name superfluous when published, an unnecessary substitute name

label: valid
definition: The name is correctly published according to the rules of nomenclature of  the ICBN
